<s>Detective-Slain</s>
<s>Cop , Suspect Fatally Shot at Station</s>
<s>WARREN , Mich. (AP )  A detective and a drug suspect were fatally wounded during a struggle while the officer was booking him at police headquarters .</s>
<s>Officers said investigators were reviewing a videotape of the lockup area in an effort to figure out the sequence of events that led to the shooting Wednesday evening .</s>
<s>Detective Christopher Wouters had arrested a suspect on drug charges , Warren police Chief James Vohs said . Both were wounded around 6:30 p.m . after the man ``produced a gun and there was a struggle ,'' he said .</s>
<s>Authorities did not immediately say whether the gun belonged to the detective or the suspect .</s>
<s>Wouters , 42 , died an hour later at St. John Macomb Hospital . The suspect died later the same night , hospital spokeswoman Rebecca O'Grady said Thursday . His name wasn't released .</s>
<s>Vohs described Wouters , a 19-year veteran , as a good officer who was married and had two young daughters . It was the first time since 1969 that an officer has been killed in the line of duty in Warren , a large blue-collar Detroit suburb .</s>